external_knowledge:
- 'Seasoned managers' refers to Managers who have been with the company for more than 5 years and received at least one promotion in the last 5 years; 
- 'climbed the corporate ladder' is a metaphor for advancement or promotion within a company; 
- 'outstanding performance' is indicated by an 'Excellent' performance rating.

- "top 3 employees" refers to the employees with the highest average monthly work hours within each department; 
- "over 2 years" refers to the time spent at the company; 
- "fewer than 2 work accidents" refers to the number of work accidents the employee has been involved in; 
- "more than 100 training hours" refers to the total training hours completed by the employee.

